---
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import portrait from "../assets/bio-portrait.jpg";
---

<BaseLayout title="Bio" description="About Zachary Sorensen McNellis.">
  <article class="document">
    <p class="label" data-animate>Bio</p>
    <h1 data-animate>About</h1>
    <hr class="rule" data-animate />
    <figure class="bio-figure" data-animate>
      <Image
        src={portrait}
        alt="Zachary and his dog Boulder at the lakeshore, snowy mountains behind them"
        class="bio-photo"
        widths={[360, 540, 720]}
        sizes="(max-width: 640px) 90vw, 320px"
      />
      <figcaption>Boulder and me, lakeside.</figcaption>
    </figure>
    <p data-animate>
      I'm originally from Charleston, South Carolina, where I grew up and where
      most of my family still lives. I'm a proud uncle, an avid rollerblader,
      and a violinist.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      Music is a constant for me. I've played violin most of my life, and I'm
      always picking up something new — mandolin, guitar, djembe, and whatever
      instrument I can get my hands on next.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      I also love to cook, and lately I've been deep into fermentation —
      tending jars of things that are slowly, happily alive.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      And you'll find me out on my skates around San Francisco — often on
      light-up wheels, usually with my dog Boulder along for the ride.
    </p>
    <p data-animate>
      More than anything, I believe we have a moral obligation to do good with
      technology. So much of tech today optimizes for the wrong things —
      engagement that tips into addiction, growth that rewards greed, a
      persistent lack of diversity, and an anxiety that all of it leaves behind.
      I don't think any of that is inevitable. I try to do my small part to
      build things that are humane, inclusive, and worth people's time.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .bio-figure {
    margin: var(--space-5) 0;
    max-width: 360px;
  }
  .bio-photo {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    display: block;
  }
  .bio-figure figcaption {
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }

  @media (min-width: 700px) {
    /* Let the portrait sit to the right of the prose on wider screens. */
    .bio-figure {
      float: right;
      max-width: 300px;
      margin: 0 0 var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    }
  }
</style>
